Dictionary which holds input parameters to an EOS which are non-standard;
this excludes `T`, `P`, `V`, `omega`, `Tc`, `Pc`, `Vc` but includes EOS
specific parameters like `S1` and `alpha_coeffs`.

eos = PRMIX(P=6e6, T=500, Tcs=[305.32, 540.2], Pcs=[4872000.0, 2740000.0], omegas=[0.098, 0.3457], zs=[.5, .5])
def to_solve(T):
    return eos.to(T=T, P=eos.P, zs=eos.zs)._spinodal_f([T, eos.P])

# Very well could be right
